Package: rottentext
Version: @VERSION@
Section: editors
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Cyril Lamy <cyril.lamy@gmail.com>
Depends: @DEPENDS@
Description: RottenText - a text editor with a sysadmin toolbox
 A text editor written in Free Pascal / Lazarus: tabs, split view, syntax
 highlighting, minimap, multiple cursors, macros, a virtual hex view for
 binaries and large files, sessions and themes.
 .
 Its differentiator is an integrated ops toolbox (Tools menu): hashes,
 .htpasswd, LDAP/LDIF, encodings and escaping, HMAC, JWT, X.509, mail trace,
 CIDR, cron, logs, YAML/JSON/TOML/INI, Kubernetes, Helm, Docker/Compose,
 Podman Quadlet, Terraform - all in-process, no external dependency.
 .
 Free software under GPL v2. Embeds the Monaspace fonts (SIL OFL 1.1); see
 /usr/share/doc/rottentext/LICENSE_THIRD_PARTIES.md
